f:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates ORDI/USDT funding rates hourly based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices, with payments occurring every hour at the top of each hour. The exchange uses its on-chain order book to determine fair value, eliminating reliance on external oracle feeds that may lag during high volatility. Funding rates are capped at ±0.75% per hour to prevent extreme payments, though ORDI's lower liquidity can still produce significant rate swings. The fully on-chain settlement ensures transparent and immutable funding calculations without counterparty risk."}]
10:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ORDI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ORDI represents the largest Bitcoin ecosystem token by market cap, making it a key barometer for BRC-20 and ordinals sentiment. Its funding rates often diverge significantly from major cryptocurrencies due to concentrated holder distribution and episodic trading volume. The pair's relatively small size on Hyperliquid creates opportunities for informed traders to capitalize on funding inefficiencies during Bitcoin network narrative shifts."}]]}]
11:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ORDI funding rates on Hyperliquid exhibit high volatility with frequent spikes above ±0.3% hourly during Bitcoin ecosystem news cycles. The token shows strong correlation with Bitcoin price movements but amplified funding rate reactions, often reaching the ±0.75% hourly cap during major ordinals protocol updates. Weekend periods typically see reduced funding rate volatility due to lower institutional participation in Bitcoin ecosystem tokens. Historical data shows ORDI funding rates averaging 15-30% higher volatility than ETH or SOL on the same exchange."}]]}]
12:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategy"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The 1-hour funding cycle on Hyperliquid creates 24 daily opportunities to capture ORDI funding payments versus the standard 3 daily payments on other exchanges. Cross-exchange arbitrage becomes particularly profitable when Hyperliquid's ORDI funding diverges from Binance or OKX by more than 0.1% hourly equivalent. Delta-neutral strategies work best during high volatility periods when ORDI funding exceeds 0.4% hourly, though position sizing must account for the token's lower liquidity. Traders should monitor Bitcoin ordinals activity and BRC-20 protocol developments as leading indicators for funding rate opportunities."}]]}]
13:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Limitations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ORDI's limited liquidity on Hyperliquid increases slippage risk during large position adjustments, particularly problematic when funding rates reverse quickly. The token's correlation with Bitcoin can break down during ordinals-specific events, creating basis risk for hedged positions. Hyperliquid's USDC-only settlement requires additional consideration for USDT exposure in the pair name, though the exchange internally handles this conversion. Smart contract risk remains elevated compared to centralized exchanges, though Hyperliquid's L1 architecture provides better security guarantees than typical DeFi protocols."}]]}]
14:["$","$L16",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does ORDI funding differ from other tokens on Hyperliquid?","answer":"ORDI exhibits higher funding rate volatility due to its Bitcoin ecosystem narrative and concentrated holder base. The token's funding rates often spike independently of broader crypto market movements, particularly during ordinals protocol updates or Bitcoin network developments."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for ORDI funding arbitrage?","answer":"Hyperliquid requires minimum $10 position sizes, but profitable ORDI funding arbitrage typically needs $1,000+ positions due to gas costs and slippage. The 0.02% maker fee structure favors larger positions that can capture multiple funding payments efficiently."},{"question":"Can I use leverage for ORDI funding rate strategies?","answer":"Hyperliquid offers up to 50x leverage on ORDI, but funding arbitrage works best with 3-5x leverage to maintain delta neutrality. Higher leverage increases liquidation risk during ORDI's frequent volatility spikes, particularly around Bitcoin halving or ordinals milestone events."},{"question":"How reliable is ORDI liquidity during funding payment times?","answer":"ORDI liquidity on Hyperliquid can thin significantly during hourly funding payments, especially during Asian trading hours. Traders should place limit orders 5-10 minutes before funding to avoid market impact, as ORDI's order book depth averages only $50K-100K on each side."}]}]
